Class GameTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.um.cps2002.tile_game.GameTest

  • public class GameTest
extends java.lang.Object
    The GameTest class tests the functionality of methods in the Game class.
    Author:
    Luke Collins & Stefania Damato

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void setup()
      This method creates a Game instance for future tests.
      void teardown()
      This method frees memory after all tests are completed.
      void testGamePlayRound()
      Tests Game.gameplayRound() by making sure that the players' moves are inputted correctly and that the map changes accordingly, so that the round runs smoothly as expected.
      void testGamePlayRoundInvalidMove()
      Tests Game.gameplayRound() by inputting a move that is invalid, since it would result in the player going outside the map.
      void testGamePlayRoundWater()
      Tests Game.gameplayRound() by checking that a player returns to the initial position after stepping on a water tile.
      void testGamePlayRoundWinner()
      Tests Game.gameplayRound() by making sure that if a player finds the treasure tile, the game stops and he/she is declared a winner.
      void testGoodPlayersGoodMapBig()
      Tests Game.setPlayersMap(int, int) with valid inputs.
      void testGoodPlayersGoodMapSmall()
      Tests Game.setPlayersMap(int, int) with valid inputs.
      void testIncorrectInput()
      Tests Game.start() with invalid user input (player number), then enters valid input.
      void testStartPlayerOnGrassTile()
      Tests Game.start() by checking that every player's initial tile is a grass tile.
      void testTooBigMap()
      Tests Game.setPlayersMap(int, int) with an invalid map size (too large).
      void testTooLittlePlayers()
      Tests Game.setPlayersMap(int, int) with an invalid number of players (too little).
      void testTooManyPlayers()
      Tests Game.setPlayersMap(int, int) with an invalid number of players (too many).
      void testTooSmallMap()
      Tests Game.setPlayersMap(int, int) with an invalid map size (too small).
